#. type: delimited block -
#: content/source/docs/rorbook/index.adoc:472
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"torquecurve\n"
"turbogas\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/source/docs/rorbook/index.adoc:475
msgid ""
"The first number is RPM where the power begins, and the second defines power "
"as a percent of total torque."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/source/docs/rorbook/index.adoc:477
msgid ""
"It's suitable to define the torque to the engine RPM set in the engine "
"definition plus 25% ( multiply the value with 1.25) to get the overev area "
"defined."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/source/docs/rorbook/index.adoc:479
msgid ""
"The following example would be good for a maximum engine RPM set to 2800."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/source/docs/rorbook/index.adoc:481
msgid "Custom curve example:"
msgstr ""

